{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"iddcac03c4-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee","identifier":"/us/usc/t2/s635"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"635"},"text":"§ 635.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Permissible revisions of concurrent resolutions on the budget","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"At any time after the concurrent resolution on the budget for a fiscal year has been agreed to pursuant to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t2/s632"},"text":"section 632 of this title","children":[],"tail":", and before the end of such fiscal year, the two Houses may adopt a concurrent resolution on the budget which revises or reaffirms the concurrent resolution on the budget for such fiscal year most recently agreed to."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"iddcac03c5-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/344/tIII/s304"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–344, title III, § 304","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1974-07-12"},"text":"July 12, 1974","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/88/310"},"text":"88 Stat. 310","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/177/tII/s201/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–177, title II, § 201(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1985-12-12"},"text":"Dec. 12, 1985","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/99/1047"},"text":"99 Stat. 1047","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/119/tII/s208/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–119, title II, § 208(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1987-09-29"},"text":"Sept. 29, 1987","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/101/786"},"text":"101 Stat. 786","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"